name: Brown Flower Shoulder Bag
description: Found: Glastonbury 2010.   These bags mimic the style of a carrier bag only the handles are that bit longer which means that they can be worn either over the shoulder or on your back which is perfect for cycling around town.  Made from a tent, this material is great for packing down so you can fold this bag in to your pocket or handbag and pull it out when you need it. Fabulous!

name: GuerillaGardening.org Tool Bag 1
description:
This Product was previously available to purchase at GROW-Selfridges Oxford Street.

Found: Reading Festival 2009.  Made in collaboration with GuerrillaGardening.org this tool bag is a stylish and convenient resting place for your outdoor essentials. The lightweight acrossâ€“body bag features a vibrant dot print and embroidered tag logo, it is a practical way to support Guerrilla Gardening in its fight against the neglect of public space, with a percentage of the sale going directly to this fabulous organisation.

# Size H 29cm W 23cm
# Closure Drawstring and toggle fastening
# Inside features Slip compartment
# Features Emboidered logo tag, adjustable shoulder strap

name: Bunting (5 metres)
description:
Bunting is made in 5m lengths.  The picture given is an example of some of the bunting I have previously made.  While all the bunting is similar be aware that due to the upcycled nature of the product patterns and colours may vary.  I can promise you that it is all very nice though.  

For custom requests please contact me by email:info@withintent.co.uk

name: Green and Silver dot
description: Found: Reading 2009.  Each shoulder bag measures 47cm x 38cm.  The handles are 63cm long and the bag can be worn on one shoulder like a tote or over both shoulders like a rucksack, which is super for cycling!!  Bags can be packed in to a small bag which is hiding away on the inside, this measures 13cm x 9cm and is uber cool.
